# Git Commits

When creating commits on behalf of the user:

- **Conventional Commits**: `type(scope): imperative summary` (`feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `docs`, `style`, `chore`) ‚Äî matches the repo history (`feat(ui): ‚Ä¶`, `test(theme): ‚Ä¶`).
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:` trailers (Cursor, Copilot, Codex, Claude, or any AI/agent identity).
- **Never** add tool-attribution lines such as `Made-with: Cursor` in commit messages.
- Plain subject line plus an optional body describing the **why**. Subject ‚â§ 72 chars.
- Do not modify `git config` `user.name` / `user.email`.
- Branch `feat/<issue>-<slug>` off `main`; PR base `main`; PR description bilingual (Arabic + English).
- Each commit is one logical change that compiles, passes `flutter analyze`, and keeps tests green.

**Cursor IDE:** disable auto-attribution under **Cursor Settings ‚Üí Agents ‚Üí Attribution** (turn off Commit Attribution and PR Attribution). If a background agent still injects a `Co-authored-by: Cursor` trailer, remove it before the commit lands.
